This week, several major companies have announced new jobs, bonuses, and higher wages for workers due to the President's tax cuts and America First policies. Starbucks is increasing worker pay and giving stock bonuses, with a total investment of over $250 million. Disney is giving a one-time cash bonus of $1,000 to over 125,000 employees and making a $50 million investment in an education program. Verizon is giving most employees 50 shares of restricted stock in anticipation of tax savings. JPMorgan Chase is unveiling a $20 billion investment plan, including wage increases for 22,000 employees, hiring 4,000 employees, and opening up to 400 new branches. Whirlpool is adding 200 jobs after the Trump Administration imposed tariffs on large residential washing machines.